The first floor is a warehouse and processing plant for refined tea, the second floor is a tea picking area, tea preservation area and office, and the third floor is a public and mother hall and living area. review: The official residence of the Keelung Fortress Command School, the official residence of the Keelung Fortress Command School during the Japanese rule of Taiwan, was registered as the monument of Keelung City in 2006. In architectural design, there is a rain shelter of more than 2 feet, a threshold of 15 cm high and an oversized drainage ditch to respond to the rainy climate of Keelung. Very local characteristics. Keelung in Qingling time is an important defensive site in North Taiwan. There are many taiwans built, and by the Japanese period, these taiwans were unified under the jurisdiction of the defense institution in Keelung Fortress. In 1902, the Keelung Fortress Command was established, and in 1928, behind the Qiuqiu Mountain, the Keelung Fortress Command Office (now 46 Xiangfeng Street) was created as the highest military command center in North Taiwan. The Fortress Command School official residence was the residence of the school officials who were stationed at the time. Close to Dashawan Beach.

Later, the monks of the Lingquan Temple of Yuemei Mountain were presided over by the master of the repair, not only the interior was fully renovated, but also the interior was fully renovated, and the name was changed to "Xinglong Temple", which was a branch of the Lingquan Temple of Yuemei Mountain. In the early years, the Buddhist library had a large number of books in Japan. After the renovation, Chinese books became large, and the books of the Dazang Sutra and Buddha Light series were on the shelves. The Master Wuzhi said that although the number is not as large as other Buddhist groups, the temple is spacious and elegant, and the windows are bright and clean. There is also a statue of the Tibetan Bodhisattva, which is made in the same mold as Fayan Temple. Everyone who has been here feels a sense of comfort and stability.
